HEADWORD: Antiphonary
<hw>An*tiph"o*na*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>antiphonarium</ets>. See <er>Antiphoner</er>.]</ety> <def>A book
containing a collection of antiphons; the book in which the antiphons of
the breviary, with their musical notes, are contained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

